snippet.title: On.BBC Question time, Home Secretary Amber Rudd is asked if Police cuts were a factor in Manchester
snippet.description:
bbqt #GE2017 ❌

ON BBC QUESTION TIME HOME SECRETARY #AmberRudd REFUSES TO ACCEPT CUTS TO POLICE WERE A FACTOR IN #Manchester ATROCITIES 

❌An audience member said Theresa May had been warned by the Police Federation that cuts in frontline officers would undermine their ability to gather low-level intelligence about possible threats. He said: “We are 20,000 police officers down and we get atrocities like this." Does the government not expect this?”
